(1337, 2000000061, '### ISO/IEC 14764 MAINTENANCE PROCESS\n\nAbran, Alain & Moore, James & Bourque, Pierre & Dupuis, Robert. (2001). Guide to the Software Engineering Body of Knowledge - Trial Version (Version 0,9). 10.13140/RG.2.2.12202.44489.\n\n#### High-Level Activities\n\nThe maintenance process comprises the following high-level activities:\n\n1.  Process implementation\n2.  Problem and modification analysis\n3.  Modification implementation\n4.  Maintenance review and acceptance\n5.  Migration\n6.  Retirement\n\nAbran, Alain & Moore, James & Bourque, Pierre & Dupuis, Robert. (2001). Guide to the Software Engineering Body of Knowledge - Trial Version (Version 0,9). 10.13140/RG.2.2.12202.44489.\n\n#### Process Implementation\n\n*   Create maintenance processes and strategies.\n*   Procedures for Modification Requests should be established.\n*   Put the CM process into action.\n\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance  A Practitioners Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n#### Problem and Modification Analysis\n\n*   Perform a preliminary investigation.\n*   Confirm the issue.\n*   Create choices for executing the change.\n*   Keep track of the outcomes.\n*   Obtain clearance for the option of modification.\n\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance  A Practitioners Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n#### Implement Modification\n\n*   Conduct a thorough investigation (analysis).\n*   The modification should be developed, coded, and tested.\n\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance  A Practitioners Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n#### Maintenance Review and Acceptance\n\n*   Conduct evaluations.\n*   Obtain approval for the change.\n\nSource: Tripathy, P., Naik K. (2014). Software Evolution and Maintenance  A Practitioners Approach. John Wiley and Son. Springer Vieweg.\n\n#### Migration\n\n*   Ascertain that the migratio